  "text": "Our results for E, χ and χ t are consistent with those of ref. [CITATION_1] . In the case of ξ 2nd we find a small deviation that we attribute to the fact that different definitions are used. In the case of ref. [CITATION_2] the definition (9) is used, while we use eq. (8) divided by the number of the sweeps. In our case, the number of the sweeps is given by stat ×(1 + n ov ). ",
